$ZIM the market is not a present-value machine. It's a forward-looking machine. If you don't understand why this has dropped since ER is because you missed the huge earnings warning for the fiscal year and the fact that the dividend (again
created_at: going forward) is predicated on profitability. So the market doesn't care about cash in hand -- at all. Only cares about 6-9 months out and this company like every one in the shipping business big or small will likely lose money next year. If they cancel the dividend
column3: this stock could be cut in half. I'm currently net-long on this stock so I have no interest on fear mongering. It's a warning for the dividend-seeking crowd to do their DD and look past the hefty dividends given in the past.
